<title>JAPAN: Japan topper capacity seen up in next 5 yrs - MITI.</title>
<headline>Japan topper capacity seen up in next 5 yrs - MITI.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's oil refineries are expected to have a topper capacity of 5.5 million barrels per day (bpd) in five years time, the Ministry of International Trade and Industry (MITI) said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>This compares with 5.2 million bpd at the end of 1996/97, ended March 31, MITI said in its five-year supply/demand outlook.</p>
<p>A breakdown of MITI's forecast for Japan's crude distillation unit (CDU) capacity and the capacity of secondary refining units follows (in 1,000 bpd):</p>
<p>	     97/98   98/99  99/2000   00/01   01/02</p>
<p>CDU	  5,232   5,299    5,401   5,478   5,536</p>
<p>reformer     721     737	754     769     783</p>
<p>cracker	818     837	856     873     889</p>
<p>-- Tokyo Energy Desk +81-3-5473-3708</p>
</text>
